column5: Any reports from Gullrock lake? The fishing is usually outstanding. I am heading up in 2 weeks to 5 lakes. It has been many years since i have fished early august. I am a late sept guy. Any tips or differences between the times for fishing is always appreciated. I know Ian will be dialed in on the fish as always. thanks to all....i do hope you all have enjoyed your canada trips so far. Safe travel and trips to all.
Google Five Lakes Lodge. Camp owner Ian Cooke usually has pics posted of recent catches.l
Looking forward to reading your trip report when you get back. Iâ€™ve seen he posts on FB with some nice catches. Might be worth to call him before you leave.

My dad is there right now on his second trip of the year. He stays at Wrights camp.He said the fishing has been pretty good, they jig with minnows and pull minnow harnesses. His last trip the spinner harness was out fishing jigs, I will see what he says on depth.
I bet you start between the old tire and that dead tree!You know where I'm talking about.You may never have to leave that spot.It's got to be a little windy tho.Have a great trip!
This made my day!!!! i do hope that old tire is on the shore.
It's not a secret spot anymore,just follow the boats to the tire.lol
